The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Tatas keen to up stake in Everest
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Tatas keen to up stake in Everest
          A STAFF REPORTER                      Talwar in Calcutta on Wednesday. A Telegraph picture                          
	Calcutta, Sept. 17: Tata Tea is open to increasing its stake in Mount Everest Mineral Water Ltd as part of its efforts to take the brand outside the country.         
	Tata Tea had acquired a 31.73 per cent stake in Mount Everest  the packaged water company that owns the Himalayan brand  through the purchase of shares from investors and a preferential allotment.        
	The option is always available to increase our stake. The rest of the ownership is quite fragmented and we will exercise the option at a strategic time, said Pradeep Poddar, managing director and CEO of Mount Everest Mineral Water.        
	At present, Himalayan has a 50 per cent market share in the estimated Rs 100-crore organic mineral water market.        
	The market for packaged water in the country is estimated at Rs 1,500 crore, of which Rs 750 crore constitute the retail market.        
	The Himalayan brand re-launch will be a great learning exercise for us in the beverage market. This will be our first step towards launching wellness-based beverage products in the country, said Sangeeta Talwar, executive director (marketing), Tata Tea Ltd.        
	According to Poddar, the brand will also look at leveraging Tata Teas distribution network in central Europe and south Asia.                                                                                                                                      
